result.execSummary:
Sean David Wilson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Sean David Wilson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Attorney Michael V Fuentes in court.  Jessica Ann Behling appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means for .  Defendant has been turned over to the State of MINNESOTA on 04/01/2022.  
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Sean David Wilson in court with attorney Melissa Nepomiachi.  Defendant Sean David Wilson in custody.  Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Minnesota.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for April 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Criminal Warrant for Commitment.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
